snippet: The malfunction was a particularly glaring failure of Russia’s space program, coming just hours after NASA landed a research probe on Mars.
abstract: Russian booster rocket carrying two telecommunications satellites malfunctions during launch, failing to deliver the satellites into their proper orbit and rendering them useless and unsalvageable; incident is yet another blow to Russia's space program.
lead_paragraph: The malfunction was a particularly glaring failure of Russia’s space program, coming just hours after NASA landed a research probe on Mars.

headline.seo: Russian Booster Rocket Fails to Deliver Satellites
headline.main: Russian Booster Rocket Fails to Deliver Satellites
